<h3>Microraptor Records</h3>

<p>It may not be the Guiness Book of World Records, but here are some
statistics on Microraptor's use:</p>

<table border="0" class="content">
  <tr>
    <td class="head">Name</td>
    <td class="head">Record</td>
    <td class="head">Holder</td>
    <td class="head">Notes</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="shortCellEm">Most Processes</td>
    <td class="shortCell">55</td>
    <td class="shortCell">Life in the Atacama</td>
    <td></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="shortCellEm">Most Simultaneous Daemons</td>
    <td class="shortCell">6</td>
    <td class="shortCell">Trestle</td>
    <td></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="shortCellEm">Longest Uptime</td>
    <td class="shortCell">~2 weeks</td>
    <td class="shortCell">Roboceptionist</td>
    <td>I'm not actually sure what the best uptime is, but the
    Roboceptionist has been running for two years with rare shutdowns,
    and I'm positive we've had at least a 2 week stretch of uptime.
    In general, Microraptor is not the cause of restarts.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="shortCellEm">Furthest South</td>
    <td class="shortCell">Atacama Desert, Chile</td>
    <td class="shortCell">Life in the Atacama</td>
    <td>Microraptor is used to control LITA's processes during their
    months-long field experiments, which occur yearly in Chile.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="shortCellEm">Greatest Depth Underwater</td>
    <td class="shortCell">100m (soon to be 200-300m)</td>
    <td class="shortCell">DEPTHX</td>
    <td></td>
  </tr>
